63.4	Barbara_Ehrenreich	Barbara Ehrenreich	Barbara Ehrenreich () born August 26, 1941, Butte, Montana is an American feminist, democratic socialist, and political activist who describes herself as "a myth buster by trade", and has been called "a veteran muckraker" by The New Yorker. During the 1980s and early 1990s she was a prominent figure in the Democratic Socialists of America. She is a widely-read and award-winning columnist and essayist, and author of 21 books.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/83/Barbara_Ehrenreich_2_by_David_Shankbone.jpg/220px-Barbara_Ehrenreich_2_by_David_Shankbone.jpg
